headline: MSCI reports higher second quarter profit on robust demand for index products
summary: Index provider MSCI reported a rise in second-quarter profit on Tuesday, as improved spending by clients drove up demand for its index products and analytics services. WHY IT'S IMPORTANT MSCI's results often reflect sentiment in the broader market, as clients use the company's stock indexes and other tools to help them evaluate their investments. KEY QUOTE "We saw more cash flows into equity ETFs tied to our indexes than any other index provider," MSCI chairman and CEO Henry Fernandez said.
